HEADWORD: Pullulate
<hw>Pul"lu*late</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>pullulatus</ets>, p. p. of <ets>pullulare</ets> to sprout, from
<ets>pullulus</ets> a young animal, a sprout, dim. of <ets>pullus</ets>.
See <er>pullet</er>.]</ety> <def>To germinate; to bud; to multiply
abundantly.</def> <rj><au>Warburton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pullulation</ent>⟦br⟧
